Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 00:00:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] QuarkPlatformPkg: relax Werror for modern GCC

The 2019 Quark baseline still inherits global GCC -Werror settings. Current
host GCC releases diagnose additional issues in shared drivers, which blocks
using this tree as a bring-up baseline.

Keep those diagnostics visible, but do not promote them to hard errors for the
Quark IA32 GCC build. This gives the workspace a buildable modern-toolchain
baseline while later patches can convert individual warnings into source fixes.
---
 QuarkPlatformPkg/Quark.dsc | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/QuarkPlatformPkg/Quark.dsc b/QuarkPlatformPkg/Quark.dsc
index 62e82a951f..cf785a96a7 100644
--- a/QuarkPlatformPkg/Quark.dsc
+++ b/QuarkPlatformPkg/Quark.dsc
@@ -938,6 +938,9 @@
   }
 !endif
 
+[BuildOptions]
+  GCC:*_*_IA32_CC_FLAGS = -Wno-error
+
 [BuildOptions.common.EDKII.DXE_RUNTIME_DRIVER]
   MSFT:*_*_*_DLINK_FLAGS = /ALIGN:4096
 
